<paragraph id="8BCC0F5CFFE0FFA0539C4651F941CA48" blockId="0.[1238,2121,596,1228]" pageId="0" pageNumber="404">• Medium to large bats with very short fur; large, flappy cheek pouches and pointy, elongated ears; dull grayto bright orange pelage, with adult males tending to be brighter than females; very broad uropatagium; and medium to very large hindclaws.</paragraph>
